INSERT [dbo].[CM_SYS_PROP_DEF] ([SYS_PROP_CD], [SYS_PROP_VAL], [SYS_PROP_DESC], [DEPRECATED], [LAST_MODIFIED]) VALUES (N'FCE_SCHEDULING_TOOL_HELP', N'<b><big>Overview</big></b> <br> This page shows the last completed and currently scheduled Inspections for facilities. Users must first select a District, but additional filtering can be performed on criteria such as <b>Facility ID</b>, <b>Facility Name</b> and <b>County</b>. <br><br> Users with appropriate system privileges will see the <b><i>Edit</i></b> button available at the bottom of the results datagrid and can create new Inspection schedules. <br><br> To gain experience in using this scheduling tool, it is useful to first work with a single facility at a time before multiple facilities (e.g., all in a County or District). <br><br> <b><big>Assign  Inspections Search Criteria</big></b> <br> <ul><li>A single <b>District</b> must be specified.</li> <li>The user can select additional search criteria if desired.</li> <li><b>Show Through FFY</b> restricts whether facility Inspections are displayed.  Inspections to be scheduled later than the Federal Fiscal Year (FFY) specified will not be shown.  This is useful if you want to concentrate on scheduling for the next year or two and do not want to see rows for facilities that only need scheduling beyond that.</li> <li><b>Show Already Scheduled</b> If checked it will additionally display the Inspections for facilities that have already been scheduled.  If not checked, facilities that have been scheduled will not be shownthis is a good check to see if you have already scheduled everything (through the FFY you specified). However, if the Inspection is not completed but has a scheduled date in the past, it will always be displayed</li> </ul>  <br>The result data grid will display some facility parameters including the <b>Facility Class and Facility Type</b>.  Additionally, it will show information about the <b>Last Completed Inspection</b> and <b>Scheduled Inspections</b> not yet completed.  <br><br><b>Last Completed Inspection</b> consists of: <ul><li><b>FFY</b>: The Federal Fiscal Year in which the inspection was completed (<b>Inspected  Date</b>).  <li><b>Evaluated Date</b>: Is the date entered into the Inspection by the Inspector as the date the inspection was completed.  <li><b>Inspector</b>: The person named in the Inspection record as the inspector. </ul> <br><b>Scheduled Inspections</b> consists of: <ul><li>Required in FFY (<b>Req. FFY</b>): Is the FFY of the scheduled Inspection (if there is one). <b>Req. FFY</b> is the FFY when the next inspection is required by the US EPA. <li><b>Next Scheduled</b>:  Is the quarter when the Inspection is scheduled to be done. <li><b>Next Assigned Staff</b>:  Is the person that this scheduled Inspection has been assigned to. </ul> <br>Note: <ul><li>Most of the facilities have one or more completed Inspections.  Only the latest Inspection is shown under the <b>Last Completed Inspection</b> column. <li>Facilities that have an Inspection scheduled in the right time frame are shown with the scheduled Inspection information in the same row as the completed Inspection. <li>A few of the facilities have no scheduled and no completed Inspections.  This will include facilities marked <b>Not Installed</b>.  No entry is made in the <b>Req. in FFY</b> fieldit is up to you to decide when and if the first Inspection should be scheduled. </ul> <br><br>If you have sufficient system privileges, you are able to edit this data grid to create additional scheduled Inspections, change staff assignments or change the scheduled quarterwithin the same FFY.  Other changes to Inspection records can only be done from the Inspection Detail page and some of those changes are restricted to users with the System Admin role. <br><br>When learning how to use this scheduler, it is recommended that you limit your search to a single or a few facilities so you are only working with a few rows at once.  It is also recommended that you check <b>Show Already Scheduled</b> so newly scheduled Inspections continue to show after you click <b>Save</b>. <br><br>Once you enter Edit mode, most of the fields under <b>Next Scheduled</b> and <b>Next Assigned Staff</b> are available for you to enter values.  <b>Next Schedule</b> can be set to any quarter from the current time through the fiscal year specified under <b>Req. FFY</b>.  You can either select a staff member or click in the check box in the <b>Inspector</b> column of the same row to assign the same person.  You can fill in as few or as many rows as you want before clicking <b>Save</b>, however for every row you enter values, you must specify both values. <br><br>You are allowed to schedule more than one Inspection for the same facility.  If not already scheduled too far out; the button, <b>Add Another</b>, will appear which if clicked will add another row that you can fill in.  The allowed scheduled quarters are from the quarter last scheduled through the fiscal year specified by <b>Req. FFY</b>. <br><br>When calculating the values for the <b>Req. FFY</b> column, the system uses the <b>Facility Type</b> and <b>Facility Class</b> values to look up an inspection interval value specified in years in the systems database. Users with administrative privileges can change these interval values if necessary.', N'(String) Full compliance evaluation scheduling help text.', N'N', CAST(1 AS Numeric(38, 0)))

